HEADWORD: Tenaillon
<hw>Te*nail"lon</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Tenaille</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Fort.)</fld> <def>A work constructed on
each side of the ravelins, to increase their strength, procure
additional ground beyond the ditch, or cover the shoulders of the
bastions.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tenancy</ent>⟦br⟧
